[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    19[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **What's wrong:** The section detection heuristic requires `stripped.upper() == stripped` (all-caps) AND ends with colon. The sample note in `__main__` uses mixed-case headers like `CHIEF COMPLAINT:`, `HISTORY OF PRESENT ILLNESS:`, `ASSESSMENT AND PLAN:` which are all-caps and will parse correctly. However, a reader might not notice the all-caps constraint and wonder why their mixed-case notes (e.g., "Assessment and Plan:") don't segment properly. The prose comment above the heuristic mentions "ASSESSMENT AND PLAN:" and "Assessment and Plan:" as examples the parser handles, but the code only handles the all-caps variant.
